-- Saudi Port Authority Signs $164 Million in Contracts, SPA Says
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-08-06T07:38:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-06/saudi-port-authority-signs-164-million-in-contracts-spa-says.html
The  Saudi Port Authority  signed
contracts valued at 615 million riyals ($164 million) to expand
its facilities, the Saudi Press Agency reported, citing
Abdulaziz al-Tuwaijri, president of the authority.  A 192 million-riyal power plant will be built at King
Abdulaziz Port in Dammam to raise capacity to 120 megawatts from
50 megawatts when completed in 24 months, the  official news
service  reported yesterday. A container terminal in Dhiba Port
and two container terminals at King Fahd Industrial Port on the
Red Sea are to be constructed within the next two and half
years, the news service said.  A terminal to service and dock passenger and leisure
vessels will be established in two years at the Yanbu Commercial
Port on the  Red Sea  to support tourism in  Saudi Arabia , the news
service said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
